					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">koitsu wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">- Many people have complained that the RF is weird and requires (at least on US TVs) to pick some insane numbered channel like 210 or 47 or something like that -- I've found this (consistently every time) to be utter nonsense.</div><br />The Japanese analog TV band plan differed from that of U.S. analog TV. The Famicom outputs on Japanese channels 1 and 2 (90-96 and 96-102 MHz), which correspond to the FM radio band on the U.S. band plan or to <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/North_American_cable_television_frequencies" class="postlink">U.S. cable TV channels</a> 95 and 96 in the so-called &quot;midband&quot;. Perhaps some TVs don't properly support these channels.</div>

